Html escaped twice for the log entry,
We have lines like this:

{code}
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] [INFO] [bamboo:unit-test]
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] [INFO] surefire unit-test configuration:
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] [INFO] &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] &lt;configuration&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO]&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;systemPropertyVariables/&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO]&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;excludes&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO]&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;exclude&gt;it/**&lt;/exclude&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO]&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;exclude&gt;**/*$*&lt;/exclude&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO]&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/excludes&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] &lt;/configuration&gt;
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] [INFO] [surefire:test]
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] [INFO] Tests are skipped.
06-Mar-2013 12:45:15	[INFO] [INFO] [bamboo:validate-manifest]
{code}

I think it's related with this line

{code}
SimpleLogEntry.java 52: return HtmlUtils.colorizeAnsiToHtml(HtmlUtils.getAsPreformattedText(log));
{code}

Colorized also escapes Html:

https://github.com/fusesource/jansi/blob/master/jansi/src/test/java/org/fusesource/jansi/HtmlAnsiOutputStreamTest.java
https://github.com/fusesource/jansi/blob/master/jansi/src/main/java/org/fusesource/jansi/HtmlAnsiOutputStream.java

Currently this variable is set in CustomPreBuildAction. 
That's too late as one of the uses is to parameterise non-default repositories to checkout the same branch as default repository. (see BAM-11544)

Move the code setting the variable to the same timepoint when we set other built-in variables like ${bamboo.buildNumber}

Currently the only logging we get about SCP tasks is this:

{code:none}
21-Feb-2013 21:36:35	Starting task 'send dist' of type 'com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.bamboo-scp-plugin:scptask'
21-Feb-2013 21:36:37	Finished task 'send dist'
{code}

Which doesn't have any indication of whether the file it was meant to send was actually there, or if there any other errors or warnings. It makes debugging SCP tasks that aren't working properly exceedingly difficult. :(

As a user I'd like to see the output of agents build logs converted to the bamboo server text encoding (or utf8)

For example, I extracted one line of a msbuild build log report contains both correctly encoded char (the date) whereas the output itself has the same letter replaced by a "," (comma)

{noformat} 
21-févr.-2013 09:53:42	7>  Cr‚ation de "PropertyEditor.dir\Release\PropertyEditor.unsuccessfulbuild", car "AlwaysCreate" a ‚t‚ sp‚cifi‚.
{noformat}

{quote}
Is there any way to get the build widgets to rotate like JIRA gadgets do?  We have many build plans and they do not all fit on the screen at once.  This means some are hidden and one must scroll the page down to see the ones at the bottom of the page.  This is not something we can do for our public display in the office.  Thanks.
{quote}

I have a custom Windows AMI to build our BitBucket repositories that have {{ssh://}} based submodules (a custom AMI is needed when using {{ssh://}} submodules with Windows. See comments on BAM-11369).

When testing using ephemeral storage for the location of the Bamboo {{build-dir}} I got the following error.
{quote}
Submodule 'common' (git@bitbucket.org:foo/bar.git) registered for path 'bar'
Cloning into 'common'...
Could not create directory '/*e*/Users/Bamboo/.ssh'.
{quote}

Note the 'e' in the path. It looks like the agent is getting confused when the {{build-dir}} is on a different drive to the home directory.

When {{build-dir}} is set to {{C:\build-dir}} the SSH keys are found correctly in {{C:\Users\Bamboo\.ssh}}
